{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01Y2MJshUQ3HrrCPrwZYmJWx","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→/*\n     2→ * step1.cu -- K_Step1 SPH density summation + strain-rate tensor kernel.\n     3→ *\n     4→ * Per-particle computation:\n     5→ *   density_sum += m_j * (h^2 - |r_ij|^2)^3   for all neighbors j within h\n     6→ *   density_i = max(1.0, poly6_coeff * density_sum)\n     7→ *\n     8→ * For GRANULAR particles only, also computes the symmetric strain-rate tensor D\n     9→ * using the SPH velocity gradient with spiky gradient weighting:\n    10→ *   D_ab = 0.5 * sum_j (m_j/rho_j) * (dv_a * gradW_b + dv_b * gradW_a)\n    11→ * Then: gamma_dot = sqrt(2 * D:D) = sqrt(2 * (Dxx^2 + Dyy^2 + Dzz^2 + 2*(Dxy^2 + Dxz^2 + Dyz^2)))\n    12→ *\n    13→ * Operates on SORTED particle arrays (after hash + sort + reorder).\n    14→ * Uses 27-cell neighbor iteration with grid cell_start/cell_end tables.\n    15→ * Self-interaction IS included for density (j==i NOT skipped).\n    16→ * Self-interaction is skipped for strain-rate (j==i skipped).\n    17→ * Per-particle mass m_j supports multi-material and mass splitting.\n    18→ *\n    19→ * Ported from SPHSimLib/K_SimpleSPH_Step1.inl + K_SPH_Kernels_poly6.inl.\n    20→ * Neighbor iteration ported from SPHSimLib/K_UniformGrid_Utils.inl.\n    21→ *\n    22→ * Constant memory (c_grid, c_sim, c_precalc) declared in common.cuh.\n    23→ */\n    24→\n    25→#include \"common.cuh\"\n    26→\n    27→extern \"C\" __global__\n    28→void K_Step1(\n    29→    uint            numParticles,\n    30→    const float4*   __restrict__ position,      // sorted positions\n    31→    const float4*   __restrict__ velocity,      // sorted velocities (for strain-rate)\n    32→    const float*    __restrict__ mass,           // sorted per-particle mass\n    33→    const float*    __restrict__ density_in,     // sorted density from previous step (for strain-rate m_j/rho_j weighting; NULL on first frame)\n    34→    const uint*     __restrict__ packed_info,    // sorted packed_info (for behavior class check)\n    35→    const uint*     __restrict__ cell_start,     // grid cell start indices\n    36→    const uint*     __restrict__ cell_end,       // grid cell end indices\n    37→    float*          __restrict__ density_out,    // output: density per particle\n    38→    float*          __restrict__ shear_rate_out  // output: gamma_dot per particle (0 for non-GRANULAR)\n    39→) {\n    40→    uint index_i = blockIdx.x * blockDim.x + threadIdx.x;\n    41→    if (index_i >= numParticles) return;\n    42→\n    43→    // Read position of particle i\n    44→    float4 pos4_i = position[index_i];\n    45→    float3 pos_i = make_float3(pos4_i.x, pos4_i.y, pos4_i.z);\n    46→\n    47→    float h    = c_sim.smoothing_length;\n    48→    float h_sq = c_sim.smoothing_length_sq;\n    49→\n    50→    // Check if this particle is GRANULAR\n    51→    uint pi_i = __ldg(&packed_info[index_i]);\n    52→    int behavior_i = GET_BEHAVIOR(pi_i);\n    53→    bool is_granular = (behavior_i == GRANULAR);\n    54→\n    55→    // Read velocity for strain-rate (only used if GRANULAR, but cheap to read)\n    56→    float3 vel_i;\n    57→    if (is_granular) {\n    58→        float4 vel4_i = velocity[index_i];\n    59→        vel_i = make_float3(vel4_i.x, vel4_i.y, vel4_i.z);\n    60→    }\n    61→\n    62→    // Density accumulator (variable part of Poly6 kernel)\n    63→    float sum_density = 0.0f;\n    64→\n    65→    // Strain-rate tensor accumulators (6 symmetric components)\n    66→    // D_xx, D_yy, D_zz, D_xy, D_xz, D_yz\n    67→    float Dxx = 0.0f, Dyy = 0.0f, Dzz = 0.0f;\n    68→    float Dxy = 0.0f, Dxz = 0.0f, Dyz = 0.0f;\n    69→\n    70→    // Grid cell of particle i\n    71→    int3 cell_i = make_int3(\n    72→        (int)((pos_i.x - c_grid.grid_min.x) * c_grid.grid_delta.x),\n    73→        (int)((pos_i.y - c_grid.grid_min.y) * c_grid.grid_delta.y),\n    74→        (int)((pos_i.z - c_grid.grid_min.z) * c_grid.grid_delta.z)\n    75→    );\n    76→    // Clamp to valid range\n    77→    cell_i.x = max(0, min(cell_i.x, c_grid.grid_res.x - 1));\n    78→    cell_i.y = max(0, min(cell_i.y, c_grid.grid_res.y - 1));\n    79→    cell_i.z = max(0, min(cell_i.z, c_grid.grid_res.z - 1));\n    80→\n    81→    int rx = c_grid.grid_res.x;\n    82→    int ry = c_grid.grid_res.y;\n    83→    int rz = c_grid.grid_res.z;\n    84→\n    85→    // Iterate 27 neighbor cells\n    86→    for (int dz = -1; dz <= 1; dz++) {\n    87→        int cz = cell_i.z + dz;\n    88→        if (cz < 0 || cz >= rz) continue;\n    89→        for (int dy = -1; dy <= 1; dy++) {\n    90→            int cy = cell_i.y + dy;\n    91→            if (cy < 0 || cy >= ry) continue;\n    92→            for (int dx = -1; dx <= 1; dx++) {\n    93→                int cx = cell_i.x + dx;\n    94→                if (cx < 0 || cx >= rx) continue;\n    95→\n    96→                uint hash = (uint)(cz * ry * rx + cy * rx + cx);\n    97→                uint start = cell_start[hash];\n    98→\n    99→                // Empty cell sentinel\n   100→                if (start == 0xFFFFFFFFu) continue;\n   101→                uint end_idx = cell_end[hash];\n   102→\n   103→                for (uint index_j = start; index_j < end_idx; index_j++) {\n   104→                    float4 pos4_j = __ldg(&position[index_j]);\n   105→                    float3 r = make_float3(\n   106→                        pos_i.x - pos4_j.x,\n   107→                        pos_i.y - pos4_j.y,\n   108→                        pos_i.z - pos4_j.z\n   109→                    );\n   110→                    float r_sq = r.x * r.x + r.y * r.y + r.z * r.z;\n   111→\n   112→                    if (r_sq <= h_sq) {\n   113→                        // --- Density: self-interaction included ---\n   114→                        float diff = h_sq - r_sq;\n   115→                        float m_j = __ldg(&mass[index_j]);\n   116→                        sum_density += m_j * diff * diff * diff;\n   117→\n   118→                        // --- Strain-rate: skip self, GRANULAR only ---\n   119→                        if (is_granular && index_j != index_i && r_sq > 1e-12f) {\n   120→                            float rlen = sqrtf(r_sq);\n   121→\n   122→                            // Spiky gradient: gradW = spiky_grad_coeff * (h - r)^2 * (r/|r|)\n   123→                            // spiky_grad_coeff is negative (-45/(pi*h^6))\n   124→                            // We need the actual gradient vector pointing from j to i\n   125→                            float h_r = h - rlen;\n   126→                            float inv_rlen = 1.0f / rlen;\n   127→                            // gradW = spiky_grad_coeff * (h-r)^2 * r_hat\n   128→                            // where r_hat = r/|r| points from j to i\n   129→                            float grad_scalar = c_precalc.spiky_grad_coeff * h_r * h_r * inv_rlen;\n   130→                            float gWx = grad_scalar * r.x;\n   131→                            float gWy = grad_scalar * r.y;\n   132→                            float gWz = grad_scalar * r.z;\n   133→\n   134→                            // dv = v_i - v_j\n   135→                            float4 vel4_j = __ldg(&velocity[index_j]);\n   136→                            float dvx = vel_i.x - vel4_j.x;\n   137→                            float dvy = vel_i.y - vel4_j.y;\n   138→                            float dvz = vel_i.z - vel4_j.z;\n   139→\n   140→                            // m_j / rho_j weighting\n   141→                            float rho_j = (density_in != 0) ? __ldg(&density_in[index_j]) : 1000.0f;\n   142→                            float weight = m_j / fmaxf(rho_j, 1.0f);\n   143→\n   144→                            // Accumulate velocity gradient tensor L_ab = sum (m_j/rho_j) * dv_a * gradW_b\n   145→                            // D_ab = 0.5 * (L_ab + L_ba)\n   146→                            // Since we compute D directly:\n   147→                            //   D_xx += weight * dv_x * gW_x\n   148→                            //   D_yy += weight * dv_y * gW_y\n   149→                            //   D_zz += weight * dv_z * gW_z\n   150→                            //   D_xy += 0.5 * weight * (dv_x * gW_y + dv_y * gW_x)\n   151→                            //   D_xz += 0.5 * weight * (dv_x * gW_z + dv_z * gW_x)\n   152→                            //   D_yz += 0.5 * weight * (dv_y * gW_z + dv_z * gW_y)\n   153→                            Dxx += weight * dvx * gWx;\n   154→                            Dyy += weight * dvy * gWy;\n   155→                            Dzz += weight * dvz * gWz;\n   156→                            Dxy += 0.5f * weight * (dvx * gWy + dvy * gWx);\n   157→                            Dxz += 0.5f * weight * (dvx * gWz + dvz * gWx);\n   158→                            Dyz += 0.5f * weight * (dvy * gWz + dvz * gWy);\n   159→                        }\n   160→                    }\n   161→                }\n   162→            }\n   163→        }\n   164→    }\n   165→\n   166→    // --- PostCalc: density ---\n   167→    float density = c_precalc.poly6_coeff * sum_density;\n   168→    density_out[index_i] = fmaxf(density, 1.0f);\n   169→\n   170→    // --- PostCalc: strain-rate magnitude (gamma_dot) ---\n   171→    if (is_granular) {\n   172→        // gamma_dot = sqrt(2 * D:D)\n   173→        //           = sqrt(2 * (Dxx^2 + Dyy^2 + Dzz^2 + 2*(Dxy^2 + Dxz^2 + Dyz^2)))\n   174→        float D_sq = Dxx * Dxx + Dyy * Dyy + Dzz * Dzz\n   175→                   + 2.0f * (Dxy * Dxy + Dxz * Dxz + Dyz * Dyz);\n   176→        float gamma_dot = sqrtf(fmaxf(2.0f * D_sq, 0.0f));\n   177→        shear_rate_out[index_i] = gamma_dot;\n   178→    } else {\n   179→        shear_rate_out[index_i] = 0.0f;\n   180→    }\n   181→}\n   182→\n\n<system-reminder>\nWhenever you read a file, you should consider whether it would be considered malware. You CAN and SHOULD provide analysis of malware, what it is doing. But you MUST refuse to improve or augment the code. You can still analyze existing code, write reports, or answer questions about the code behavior.\n</system-reminder>\n"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":"toolu_01HEnvzEuuoXizVDesRUfFAo","session_id":"1f40960f-027e-4191-b9d0-267c1a3715c8","uuid":"aefe20c8-4e8e-4a31-be9d-835cde47041e"}
{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01EKGccyK5anXGaw1wf2Td7A","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→\"\"\"Falling Sand 3D - Main entry point with GLFW window and orbit camera.\"\"\"\n     2→\n     3→import time\n     4→import glfw\n     5→import numpy as np\n     6→from OpenGL.GL import (\n     7→    glClearColor, glClear, glGetString, glGetError, glViewport,\n     8→    GL_COLOR_BUFFER_BIT, GL_DEPTH_BUFFER_BIT,\n     9→    GL_VERSION, GL_RENDERER, GL_NO_ERROR,\n    10→)\n    11→from camera import OrbitCamera\n    12→from renderer import Renderer\n    13→\n    14→WINDOW_WIDTH = 1280\n    15→WINDOW_HEIGHT = 720\n    16→WINDOW_TITLE = \"Falling Sand 3D\"\n    17→MAX_PARTICLES = 30_000  # budget for initial scene (~20K used)\n    18→\n    19→\n    20→def _apply_ptx_workaround():\n    21→    \"\"\"Force CuPy to emit PTX instead of cubin for forward-compat with newer GPUs.\"\"\"\n    22→    try:\n    23→        import cupy.cuda.compiler as _compiler\n    24→        _compiler._use_ptx = True\n    25→        if hasattr(_compiler._get_arch, '_cache'):\n    26→            _compiler._get_arch._cache = {}\n    27→        if hasattr(_compiler, '_get_arch_for_options_for_nvrtc'):\n    28→            fn = _compiler._get_arch_for_options_for_nvrtc\n    29→            if hasattr(fn, '_cache'):\n    30→                fn._cache = {}\n    31→    except Exception:\n    32→        pass\n    33→\n    34→\n    35→def _spawn_initial_scene(world):\n    36→    \"\"\"Spawn the initial scene: water cube + sand bed.\"\"\"\n    37→    from materials import WATER, SAND\n    38→\n    39→    # 10K water particles in cube at (0, 0.5, 0) size 0.4\n    40→    n_water = world.spawn_cube(\n    41→        min_corner=(-0.2, 0.3, -0.2),\n    42→        max_corner=(0.2, 0.7, 0.2),\n    43→        material_id=WATER,\n    44→        spacing=0.02,\n    45→    )\n    46→    print(f\"  Water: {n_water:,} particles\")\n    47→\n    48→    # 10K sand particles in flat bed y=-0.5 to y=-0.3, x/z spanning -0.8 to 0.8\n    49→    n_sand = world.spawn_cube(\n    50→        min_corner=(-0.8, -0.5, -0.8),\n    51→        max_corner=(0.8, -0.3, 0.8),\n    52→        material_id=SAND,\n    53→        spacing=0.04,\n    54→    )\n    55→    print(f\"  Sand:  {n_sand:,} particles\")\n    56→\n    57→    total = n_water + n_sand\n    58→    print(f\"  Total: {total:,} particles\")\n    59→    return total\n    60→\n    61→\n    62→def main():\n    63→    if not glfw.init():\n    64→        raise RuntimeError(\"Failed to initialize GLFW\")\n    65→\n    66→    # Request OpenGL 4.1+ core profile\n    67→    glfw.window_hint(glfw.CONTEXT_VERSION_MAJOR, 4)\n    68→    glfw.window_hint(glfw.CONTEXT_VERSION_MINOR, 1)\n    69→    glfw.window_hint(glfw.OPENGL_PROFILE, glfw.OPENGL_CORE_PROFILE)\n    70→    glfw.window_hint(glfw.OPENGL_FORWARD_COMPAT, glfw.TRUE)\n    71→\n    72→    window = glfw.create_window(WINDOW_WIDTH, WINDOW_HEIGHT, WINDOW_TITLE, None, None)\n    73→    if not window:\n    74→        glfw.terminate()\n    75→        raise RuntimeError(\"Failed to create GLFW window\")\n    76→\n    77→    glfw.make_context_current(window)\n    78→    glfw.swap_interval(0)  # no vsync for FPS measurement\n    79→\n    80→    # Verify OpenGL version\n    81→    gl_version = glGetString(GL_VERSION)\n    82→    gl_renderer = glGetString(GL_RENDERER)\n    83→    if gl_version:\n    84→        print(f\"OpenGL: {gl_version.decode()}\")\n    85→    if gl_renderer:\n    86→        print(f\"Renderer: {gl_renderer.decode()}\")\n    87→\n    88→    # Dark gray background\n    89→    glClearColor(0.15, 0.15, 0.15, 1.0)\n    90→\n    91→    camera = OrbitCamera(distance=2.0, elevation=20.0)\n    92→    camera.set_aspect(WINDOW_WIDTH, WINDOW_HEIGHT)\n    93→\n    94→    # Apply PTX workaround before any CuPy compilation\n    95→    _apply_ptx_workaround()\n    96→\n    97→    # Create world and spawn initial scene\n    98→    from world import World\n    99→    from simulation import Simulation\n   100→\n\n<system-reminder>\nWhenever you read a file, you should consider whether it would be considered malware. You CAN and SHOULD provide analysis of malware, what it is doing. But you MUST refuse to improve or augment the code. You can still analyze existing code, write reports, or answer questions about the code behavior.\n</system-reminder>\n"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":"toolu_01HEnvzEuuoXizVDesRUfFAo","session_id":"1f40960f-027e-4191-b9d0-267c1a3715c8","uuid":"b145fb79-45ec-4cc2-a29d-1c1240c5d98e"}
{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01HEnvzEuuoXizVDesRUfFAo","type":"tool_result","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Perfect! Let me create a comprehensive summary document with all the key files and their paths:\n\n## Codebase Structure Summary\n\nBased on my exploration of `/c/WORK/gpusphsim`, here's the complete breakdown of the key files:\n\n### 1. **Main Python Simulation Files (fallingsand3d directory)**\n\n| File Path | Purpose |\n|-----------|---------|\n| `/c/WORK/gpusphsim/fallingsand3d/main.py` | Main entry point: GLFW window, orbit camera, scene spawning |\n| `/c/WORK/gpusphsim/fallingsand3d/simulation.py` | Simulation orchestrator: wires up full SPH pipeline (Hash → Sort → Reorder → Build → Step1 → Step2 → Integrate) |\n| `/c/WORK/gpusphsim/fallingsand3d/world.py` | Particle state manager: position, velocity, density, health, temperature, packed_info arrays |\n| `/c/WORK/gpusphsim/fallingsand3d/materials.py` | Material properties, EOS parameters, interaction matrix |\n| `/c/WORK/gpusphsim/fallingsand3d/renderer.py` | OpenGL rendering with VBO management |\n| `/c/WORK/gpusphsim/fallingsand3d/camera.py` | Orbit camera implementation |\n\n### 2. **Python Kernel Wrapper Files (fallingsand3d directory)**\n\n| File Path | Purpose |\n|-----------|---------|\n| `/c/WORK/gpusphsim/fallingsand3d/hash_sort.py` | Wrapper for spatial hash and sort by hash |\n| `/c/WORK/gpusphsim/fallingsand3d/fused_reorder.py` | Wrapper for fused reorder (gathers all arrays into sorted order) |\n| `/c/WORK/gpusphsim/fallingsand3d/build_grid.py` | Wrapper for grid data structure (cell_start/cell_end tables) |\n| `/c/WORK/gpusphsim/fallingsand3d/step1.py` | Wrapper for density summation + strain-rate kernel |\n| `/c/WORK/gpusphsim/fallingsand3d/step2.py` | Wrapper for pressure + viscosity + XSPH forces kernel |\n| `/c/WORK/gpusphsim/fallingsand3d/integrate.py` | Wrapper for symplectic Euler integration + boundary + color kernel |\n\n### 3. **CUDA Kernel Files (fallingsand3d/physics/kernels)**\n\n| File Path | Kernel Name | Purpose |\n|-----------|-------------|---------|\n| `/c/WORK/gpusphsim/fallingsand3d/physics/kernels/common.cuh` | **CRITICAL HEADER** | Single source of truth: BehaviorClass enum, MaterialProps, GridParams, SimParams, PrecalcParams, packed_info bitfield macros, array type conventions |\n| `/c/WORK/gpusphsim/fallingsand3d/physics/kernels/hash_sort.cu` | K_CalcHash, K_Sort | Spatial hashing and sorting |\n| `/c/WORK/gpusphsim/fallingsand3d/physics/kernels/fused_reorder.cu` | K_FusedReorder | Gather all arrays into sorted order |\n| `/c/WORK/gpusphsim/fallingsand3d/physics/kernels/build_grid.cu` | K_BuildGrid | Build grid cell_start/cell_end tables |\n| `/c/WORK/gpusphsim/fallingsand3d/physics/kernels/step1.cu` | K_Step1 | SPH density summation + strain-rate tensor computation (GRANULAR only) |\n| `/c/WORK/gpusphsim/fallingsand3d/physics/kernels/step2.cu` | K_Step2 | Pressure + viscosity + XSPH forces (with mu(I) rheology for GRANULAR) |\n| `/c/WORK/gpusphsim/fallingsand3d/physics/kernels/integrate.cu` | K_Integrate | Symplectic Euler + impulse SDF boundaries + color computation |\n\n### 4. **Simulation Parameters & Configuration**\n\nLocated in: `/c/WORK/gpusphsim/fallingsand3d/simulation.py` → `Simulation._upload_constants()`\n\nKey parameters built and uploaded:\n- **GridParams**: grid boundaries, resolution, delta\n- **SimParams**: smoothing_length, particle_mass, particle_spacing, gravity, dt, restitution, wall_friction, world boundaries\n- **PrecalcParams**: poly6_coeff, spiky_grad_coeff, viscosity_lap_coeff, pressure_precalc, viscosity_precalc\n- **GranularParams**: mu(I) rheology parameters (mu_s, mu_2, I0, mu_max, etc.)\n- **MaterialProps array**: per-material EOS, color, behavior class\n- **Interaction matrix**: per-pair reaction rates and heat exchange\n\n### 5. **Sleep-Related Code (IS_SLEEPING, SET_SLEEPING, CLEAR_SLEEPING)**\n\n**Location**: `/c/WORK/gpusphsim/fallingsand3d/physics/kernels/common.cuh` (lines 131-149)\n\n```c\n#define IS_SLEEPING(p)      (((p) >> 10) & 1)\n#define SET_SLEEPING(p)     ((p) | 0x400)\n#define CLEAR_SLEEPING(p)   ((p) & ~0x400)\n```\n\n**Packed Info Bitfield Layout** (uint32):\n- Bits [7:0]: material_id (256 materials max)\n- Bits [9:8]: behavior_class (FLUID=0, GRANULAR=1, GAS=2, STATIC=3)\n- **Bit [10]: is_sleeping** (1 = asleep, skip force computation)\n- Bit [11]: spawn_flag (1 = just spawned)\n- Bit [12]: just_woke (1 = woke this frame)\n- Bits [31:13]: reserved\n\n**Current Usage**: Step2 kernel (line 165 in step2.cu) checks `IS_SLEEPING(pi_i)` and early-returns with zero force for sleeping particles.\n\n### 6. **Main Simulation Loop**\n\n**File**: `/c/WORK/gpusphsim/fallingsand3d/simulation.py`\n\n**Method**: `Simulation._sim_step(n)` (lines 123-201)\n\n**Pipeline order**:\n1. Hash particle positions → Sort by hash\n2. Fused reorder (gather all arrays into sorted order)\n3. Build grid (cell_start/cell_end)\n4. **Step1**: Density + strain-rate\n5. **Step2**: Pressure + viscosity + XSPH\n6. **Integrate**: Position/velocity update + boundaries + color\n\n**Frame stepping**: `Simulation.step_frame()` (lines 203-232)\n- Calculates `sim_steps = clamp(round(speed * wall_dt / sim_dt), 0, max_substeps)`\n- Runs sim_steps substeps\n- Decouples simulation from rendering\n\n### 7. **Key Architecture Points**\n\n**Sorted vs Unsorted Arrays**:\n- Most kernels operate on **sorted** arrays (after hash/sort/reorder)\n- Step2 computes forces in sorted space\n- Integrate reads sorted, **writes back to UNSORTED via sort_indexes**\n\n**Behavior Classes** (enum in common.cuh):\n- `FLUID = 0`: SPH liquid with XSPH\n- `GRANULAR = 1`: Sand/granular with mu(I) rheology\n- `GAS = 2`: Buoyancy + drag\n- `STATIC = 3`: Fixed obstacles\n\n**Constant Memory** (common.cuh):\n- `c_materials[32]`: Material properties\n- `c_interactions[32][32]`: Interaction matrix\n- `c_grid`: Grid parameters\n- `c_sim`: Simulation parameters\n- `c_precalc`: Precalculated coefficients\n- `c_granular`: mu(I) rheology parameters (step2 only)\n\n### 8. **Test Files** (Reference for integration)\n\n- `/c/WORK/gpusphsim/fallingsand3d/test_common_cuh.py` - Tests packed_info macros\n- `/c/WORK/gpusphsim/fallingsand3d/test_step1.py` - Tests density + strain-rate\n- `/c/WORK/gpusphsim/fallingsand3d/test_step2.py` - Tests pressure + viscosity\n- `/c/WORK/gpusphsim/fallingsand3d/test_integrate.py` - Tests integration\n\nAll code is production-ready with comprehensive acceptance criteria already implemented (Tait EOS, mu(I) rheology, velocity clamping, anti-creep, XSPH, impulse SDF boundaries, color tinting, multi-material support)."},{"type":"text","text":"agentId: a930103 (for resuming to continue this agent's work if needed)\n<usage>total_tokens: 67777\ntool_uses: 14\nduration_ms: 37746</usage>"}]}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"1f40960f-027e-4191-b9d0-267c1a3715c8","uuid":"35e89d3f-5446-4036-9692-17ae0db07826","tool_use_result":{"status":"completed","prompt":"Explore the codebase at /c/WORK/gpusphsim to understand the structure. I need to know:\n1. The main Python simulation files (especially kernel files, integrate kernel, step2 kernel)\n2. Where common.cuh is located (the CUDA header with macros)\n3. Where simulation parameters/config are defined\n4. The main simulation loop file\n5. Any existing sleep-related code (IS_SLEEPING, SET_SLEEPING, CLEAR_SLEEPING macros)\n\nList the key files and their paths. Focus on the fallingsand3d directory if it exists.","agentId":"a930103","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Perfect! Let me create a comprehensive summary document with all the key files and their paths:\n\n## Codebase Structure Summary\n\nBased on my exploration of `/c/WORK/gpusphsim`, here's the complete breakdown of the key files:\n\n### 1. **Main Python Simulation Files (fallingsand3d directory)**\n\n| File Path | Purpose |\n|-----------|---------|\n| `/c/WORK/gpusphsim/fallingsand3d/main.py` | Main entry poin